        "text": "The RStudio Linux instructions on 'Install required dependencies' (<https:\/\/docs.rstudio.com\/resources\/install-r-source\/#install-required-dependencies>) requires setting up third-party repositories in order to leverage those to install dependencies. This is something many sysadms are hesitant to do. They often prefer to install from official repositories only.  Because of this, it's better to have an explicit list of dependencies (similar to what RStudio's 'SUSE Linux' instruction provides).",
