        "client_msg_id": "0c2be402-8b71-4ac5-859f-c76af587830d",
        "text": "Also, the RStudio build instructions (<https:\/\/docs.rstudio.com\/resources\/install-r-source\/#build-and-install-r>) does _not_ explain why the different configure options are used, e.g. `--enable-R-shlib` is required if you want to run R via the RStudio Desktop. I think that too could make \"install R from source\" less intimidating and maybe even become a go-to solution for all users out there without admin rights.",
